AML transaction-screening agent — Cline rules.

Screen the transactions in data/ for money-laundering red flags and draft a
SAR-style narrative grounded only in what the rules flagged. The rules in tools/
do all detection; you pick which rules to run and read the flags, and never judge
an amount, date, or country yourself.

For every screening:
1. python -m tools.screen --json > reports/_flags.json
   (add --rule <name> for structuring, round_number, high_risk_jurisdiction, or velocity)
2. Read reports/_flags.json and group the flags by account.
3. Write a SAR narrative; after every assertion cite the transaction id and rule,
   e.g. "(T010, T011, T012 — structuring)".
4. Check that every claim traces to a flag and that no flag was dropped; revise.
5. Save the narrative and flags to reports/sar_<date>.md.

Every flag in the narrative must come from a tool result, never invented. If no
transaction fires, write "No suspicious activity detected by the configured
rules." Run tests with: python -m pytest -q
